1.00	Rothesay_(Scotland)	Rothesay, Bute	The town of Rothesay (Scottish Gaelic: ) is the principal town on the Isle of Bute, in the council area of Argyll and Bute, Scotland. It can be reached by ferry from Wemyss Bay which offers an onward rail link to Glasgow. At the centre of the town is Rothesay Castle, a ruined castle which dates back to the 13th century, and which is unique in Scotland for its circular plan. Rothesay lies along the coast of the Firth of Clyde.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Rothesay_Pier_-_geograph.org.uk_-_31029.jpg/240px-Rothesay_Pier_-_geograph.org.uk_-_31029.jpg
